cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper discusses privacy and security challenges in the IoT domain, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes methodologies to analyze privacy policies and improve their effectiveness, which involves software engineering techniques (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the need for user understanding and control over their data, which relates to the field of cyberpsychology (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper proposes a method to find inconsistencies between IoT devices and their privacy policies, which involves system integration (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects.
